        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 6 at 2:50PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 249 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Elgin, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hoffman Estates, Fox River Grove, Barrington, Carpentersville,
Algonquin, Port Barrington, Lake Barrington, West Dundee, East
Dundee, Cary, Elgin, South Elgin, South Barrington, North Barrington,
Gilberts, Streamwood, Tower Lakes, Pingree Grove, Trout Valley,
Barrington Hills, Sleepy Hollow, Inverness, Hanover Park, Valley
View, and Wauconda.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
